<td width="10"><img src="http://www.maximumeq.com/forum/Images/SmallNew.gif" border="0" alt="New Message"></td><td width="50%"><font face="Verdana" size="1" color="EEEEEE"><b>Here's a decent idea... (modified 0 times)</b> </font></td><td width="50%" align="RIGHT"><font face="Verdana" size="1" color="EEEEEE"><b>Orocular</b></font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="DDDDDD">
<td><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" align="CENTER">
<tr>
<td><a href="UltraBoard.cgi?Action=ShowProfile&ID=orocular&Board=wizard&Idle=30&Sort=0&Order=Descend&Page=0&Session=" target="Profile" OnMouseOver="window.status='View Orocular (orocular) Profile.';return true;" OnMouseOut="window.status=''"><font face="Verdana" size="1" color="000000 ">Profile</font></a><font face="Verdana" size="1" color="000000 "> | </font><a href="mailto:Orocular@hotmail.com" OnMouseOver="window.status='Send email to Orocular.';return true;" OnMouseOut="window.status=''"><font face="Verdana" size="1" color="000000 ">Email</font></a></td><td align="RIGHT"></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="EEEEEE">
<td><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="5" cellpadding="5" align="CENTER">
<tr>
<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">At your level you should get a group of decent individuals you trust together... and go to the Kerra Isle in Erudes crossing. It will take a full group to go with you and have a tank and a healer. The reason I say take others with you is due to the fact that the wisps on the island generaly hit rather hard for lvl 8... as they hit for well into the twenties on occasion. Now the way to go about this as a wizard (at lvl 12 you can solo these) is to root it from a minor distance away (just out of melee range). At this time you have your tanks and others attack the beast. The wisp will argo on the first thing that hits it. If you get resisted run to your tank and have him assist you... but do not enter melee just yet. When your tank gets it off you then go ahead go straight for the nuke. Use your highest nuke... it will stay on the tank. It would be wise to have a bard and a druid with you as well. Both for the healing support they provide. Once again... full group, tank and healer mandatory, other 3 slots can be filled with anything. Good luck to you. BTW Get bound at the Qeynos docks so you don't have to wait for the boat long if death occurs.<hr>Orocular Goodheart<br>
Apprentice of Master Tashim<br>
Student of The Wyrd<br>
Keepers of Oak<br>
The Rathe</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="DDDDDD">
